<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="b7f19b29-5631-562f-b75c-8f51593886f3" activityNameId="d8fbd861-07be-493d-925d-8a41488a486f" parentActivityId="8a81ac4f-153f-52cf-ac9d-28ba27e8cbd8" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">corrugated board box production</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The process starts as reels of Fluting Medium and Linerboard are fed into a machine called a Corrugator.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with folded “corrugated board boxes” ready for delivery.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Corrugated Board is manufactured from several specially conditioned layers of recycled or virgin papers, with the Fluting Medium being the middle layer and Linerboard used for the outside layers. Reels of Fluting Medium and Linerboard are fed into a machine which is called a Corrugator (FEFCO, 2021). In integrated plants such as the ones represented here, the finished board is further folded into boxes.</text>
          <imageUrl index="1">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/fb7c96f2-1933-4a81-a33a-515d0a5fb151</imageUrl>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">The data on corrugated board production are based on 470 plants (mostly integrated plants with corrugated board and box production on the same site) in Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, the Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Russia, Serbia, Slovakia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Turkey and the United Kingdom. Together they produced 18,730,000 tonnes saleable product, which is 73% of the total annual production of corrugated board products in Europe. Each of the production sites produces on average 33.600 tonnes of corrugated sheets, ranging from 329– 148.000 tonnes each. Reference(s): https://www.fefco.org/sites/default/files/documents/2022-07-07_FEFCO%20LCA%202021.pdf, last accessed March 2023</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">For this dataset the European average of recycled and virgin paper inputs (wellenstoff, semichemical fluting, kraftliner, testliner) was used.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">The following air emissions were reported in the study: Particulates, &lt;2.5μm, Particulates, &gt;2.5μm and &lt;10μm, Particulates, &gt;10μm, CO2 (fossil), CO2 (biomass) , NOx (as NO2) , SOx (as SO2) .</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">For a more complete air emission profile, additional air emissions (beyond the ones listed above) were added for the combustion of the external fuels using LCI datasets for combustion of different fuels as proxy. The air emissions were calculated based on the mix of the external fuels in the study. More information about the fuel mix and the proxy are provided under "Extrapolations".</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="5682ee05-067a-4dd3-a2b5-93f3f1d25c75">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">1702:Manufacture of corrugated paper and paperboard and of containers of paper a</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0723d252-7e2a-11de-9820-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RER</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Data for main producers in Europe (Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, the Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Russia, Serbia, Slovakia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Turkey and the United Kingdom)</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Average of present used technology</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The Fluting Medium paper is conditioned with heat and steam and fed between large corrugating rolls that give the paper its fluted shape in the Single Facer. Starch is applied to the tips of the flutes on one side and the inner liner is glued to the fluting. The corrugated fluting medium with liner attached to it is called single face web and travels along the machine towards the Double Backer where the single face web meets the outer liner and forms corrugated board. A number of layers of single faced web may be built up to produce double and triple wall corrugated board. The corrugated board is slit into the required widths and cut into sheets which are then stacked or palletised. The final stage of the process consists of printing and then slotting, folding and gluing the corrugated board to manufacture a corrugated box.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2021-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
